install vmware tools

step 1 : mount vitual CD
from top menu bar select : VM > install VMware tools ----> virtual CD mounted
check among floppy and CD's - 
You'll see : VMware tools  : open it - copy tar.gz file to desktop - extract it on desktop

now you have : vmware-tools-distrib , on your desktop
step2 : 
cd Desktop/vmware-tools-distrib
 
sudo ./vmware-install.pl -d

Enter your Ubuntu password.

Restart the Ubuntu virtual machine after the VMware Tools installation completes
